Sentencas: Sr1-xLaxTiO3 (SLT; 0 <= x <= 0.5) powder samples were synthesised at room temperature by a mechanochemical method from SrO, La2O3 and TiO2 mixtures in 90 min.
Titulo: Mechanosynthesis of Sr1-xLaxTiO3 anodes for SOFCs: Structure and electrical conductivity

Sentencas: The obtained SLT samples as potential anode materials in solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) were investigated.
Titulo: Mechanosynthesis of Sr1-xLaxTiO3 anodes for SOFCs: Structure and electrical conductivity

Sentencas: The microstructure, electrical conductivity and chemical compatibility with yttria-stabilised zirconia (YSZ) were studied.
Titulo: Mechanosynthesis of Sr1-xLaxTiO3 anodes for SOFCs: Structure and electrical conductivity

Sentencas: The powder samples had a nanometric character after milling.
Titulo: Mechanosynthesis of Sr1-xLaxTiO3 anodes for SOFCs: Structure and electrical conductivity

Sentencas: After a subsequently heating at 900 degrees C, the particle size slightly increased, but still remained nanometric.
Titulo: Mechanosynthesis of Sr1-xLaxTiO3 anodes for SOFCs: Structure and electrical conductivity

Sentencas: At this high temperature, a good chemical compatibility with YSZ was found.
Titulo: Mechanosynthesis of Sr1-xLaxTiO3 anodes for SOFCs: Structure and electrical conductivity

Sentencas: The x = 0.2 sample gave the best electrical conductivity values, i.e. 0.23 W cm(-2).
Titulo: Mechanosynthesis of Sr1-xLaxTiO3 anodes for SOFCs: Structure and electrical conductivity

Sentencas: These features make such as-obtained samples good candidates to be used as anodes in SOFCs.
Titulo: Mechanosynthesis of Sr1-xLaxTiO3 anodes for SOFCs: Structure and electrical conductivity
